http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/NGT-bars-construction-at-night/article14020047.ece

The Southern Bench of the National Green Tribunal has granted an interim injunction against a construction company from carrying out construction activity on Seshadri Road, Alwarpet, during night hours.The Bench comprising Justice P. Jyothimani and expert member P.S. Rao granted the injunction on Friday last, while hearing an application filed by petitioners Sashi Kumar B. Menon and Zaheer Ahmed Sayeed, residents of ‘Palmwoods’ on Seshadri Road.They had objected to construction by M/s Baashyam Constructions Pvt. Ltd. at Sadhar Gardens during the night hours after 6 pm.The Bench further directed the issuing of notice to authorities concerned, including the Chennai Police Commissioner, the Chennai Metropolitan Development Authority (CMDA), the Corporation of Chennai and the Tamil Nadu Pollution Control Board (TNPCB) and private notice to M/s Baashyam Constructions Pvt. Ltd. to appear before it on February 9.Petition opposes building activity on Seshadri Road after 6 pm